<strong>Note</strong>: Care should be taken to actually kill the plant when it’s harvested. Glossy buckthorn has historically been coppiced. This means it was cut at the ground to promote regrowth providing a continual harvest from the same shrub. Without an application of herbicide to the cut stump, the shrub will simply sprout and regrow. I would be interested to know if defoliating glossy buckthorn in the summer would kill it.
